EngLawArticles.EngArticleContent:
Those in any one of the following circumstances shall not be deemed as a responsible person; those already in the aforementioned role but falling under one of the following circumstances shall be removed from the position:
1. Those in any one of the situations in Subparagraph 2, Paragraph 1, Article 10 of the Satellite Broadcasting Act;
2. Those who were once deemed as a responsible person, where the execution of his/her duties caused the business license to be revoked;
3. Those who have been sentenced to imprisonment for embezzlement, the custodial sentence of which has not concluded or five years have not lapsed since the date of conclusion of the custodial sentence, the expiration of probation period, or the pardon of such punishment;
4. Those without domestic residence; or
5. Those with other serious problems that are deemed as unsuitable for being a responsible person.
